## Motivation

TLDR: This PR now enforces valid package names when running `leo init` and `leo new`. In addition, we now will output the number of constraints during `leo build` by default. Adds CircleCI to resolve our flaky test issues from Github Actions.

- Adds safety check for valid package names
- Removes use of 'Default' in Leo CLI
- Renames `leo update` command's  `Sub` to `Automatic`
- Renames all instances of `ctx` to `context`
- Outputs the number of constraints during `leo build`
- Resolves flaky tests from Github Actions

## Test Plan

Adds unit tests to check package validity.
```rust
#[test]
fn test_is_package_name_valid() {
    assert!(Package::is_package_name_valid("foo"));
    assert!(Package::is_package_name_valid("foo-bar"));
    assert!(Package::is_package_name_valid("foo-bar-baz"));

    assert!(!Package::is_package_name_valid(""));
    assert!(!Package::is_package_name_valid("-"));
    assert!(!Package::is_package_name_valid("-foo"));
    assert!(!Package::is_package_name_valid("-foo-"));
    assert!(!Package::is_package_name_valid("foo--bar"));
    assert!(!Package::is_package_name_valid("foo---bar"));
    assert!(!Package::is_package_name_valid("foo--bar--baz"));
    assert!(!Package::is_package_name_valid("foo---bar---baz"));
    assert!(!Package::is_package_name_valid("foo*bar"));
    assert!(!Package::is_package_name_valid("foo,bar"));
    assert!(!Package::is_package_name_valid("foo_bar"));
}
```

As part of migrating to CircleCI, we are now compiling the local version of Leo once, and running it on all of the end-to-end tests in parallel, saving time and resources.

